item.title: JDK Problems
item.dc:creator: @primadude Primadude
item.description:
@primadude wrote:

[quote=“Bmaw, post:5, topic:260441”][quote author=primadude link=topic=343873.msg2655330#msg2655330 date=1233804916]

I go to compile my server and it says “You do not have JDK 6 or 6”
I JUST downloaded 6u12.
Anyone know whats wrong???

Change the directory leading to JDK in the compiling batch file you are running, to the directory that works with you.

This might possibly work:

@echo off "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_12\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause

[/quote]nope no luck[br][br][size=1]Posted on: February 04, 2009, 09:37:37 pm[/size][hr]Well actually with that one (Primadude) it no longer says i need JDK its just a blank box,[/quote]

Thats because it is compiling.
Wait until it says ‘Press any key to continue.’ - That means it has successfully compiled.
